<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="multiple">
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Taxon classification Animalia Hymenoptera Chrysididae</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrier, 1869" authorityName="Chevrier" authorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum gerstaeckeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gerstaeckeri">Hedychrum gerstaeckeri Chevrier, 1869</taxonomicName>
Figs 56, 61
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum Gerstaeckeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="Gerstaeckeri">
<pageBreakToken pageId="30" pageNumber="31" start="start">Hedychrum</pageBreakToken>
Gerstaeckeri
</taxonomicName>
Chevrier, 1869: 47.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Length 4-8 mm. The female differs from the females of other 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hedychrum</taxonomicName>
species by having a completely blue, violet-blue or green-blue mesosoma. As in 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum rutilans" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilans">Hedychrum rutilans</taxonomicName>
, the female does not have an apicomedial tubercle on S3. Both sexes also have medially pale brown or yellowish mandibles. The male is similar to the female in colouration and can be confused with the males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum niemelai" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niemelai">Hedychrum niemelai</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum nobile" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobile">Hedychrum nobile</taxonomicName>
. However, the punctation of T3 is coarser in 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum gerstaeckeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gerstaeckeri">Hedychrum gerstaeckeri</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 61) and the mesotibial groove is longer and deeper (Fig. 56).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Denmark, Estonia, Finland, Latvia, Lithuania. Relatively common. - Trans-Palearctic: from western Europe to Japan, China and Taiwan (
<bibRefCitation author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 128" title="An annotated checklist of the chrysidid wasps (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae) from China." url="10.3897/zookeys.455.6557" volume="455" year="2014">Rosa et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="biology">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Habitat: sparsely vegetated sandy areas, dry meadows. Adults often visit flowers of 
<taxonomicName authority="Steud., 1840" authorityName="Steud." authorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Heteroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heteroptera" order="Apiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Apiaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Heteroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heteroptera" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Heteroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heteroptera" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Euphorbiaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Trautmann, W" journalOrPublisher="Uschman, Weimar" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" title="Die Goldwespen Europas." year="1927">Trautmann 1927</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kusdas, K" journalOrPublisher="Naturkundliches Jahrbuch der Stadt Linz" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="307 - 326" title="Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Goldwespenfauna (Chrysididae und Cleptidae) Oberoesterreichs, unter besonderer Beruecksichtigung des Grossraumes von Linz. 2. Nachtrag." volume="1956" year="1956">Kusdas 1956</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kunz, PX" journalOrPublisher="Beihefte zu den Veroeffentlichungen fuer Naturschutz und Landschaftspflege in Baden-Wuerttemberg" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 188" title="Die Goldwespen (Chrysididae) Baden-Wuerttembergs. Taxonomie, Bestimmung, Verbreitung, Kartierung und Oekologie. - Mit einem Bestimmungsschluessel fuer die deutschen Arten." volume="77" year="1994">Kunz 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Veroeffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzern" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" pagination="1 - 139" title="Die Goldwespen der Schweiz." volume="9" year="1997">Linsenmaier 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Univ., Tuebingen" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" title="Faunistik und Oekologie der HymenopteraAculeata des Tuebinger Gebiets, vor allem des Spitzbergs, unter besonderer Beruecksichtigung der in Holz und Pflanzenstengeln nistenden Arten. Diss." year="1979">Westrich 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="Giornale Italiano di Entomologia" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" pagination="79 - 90" title="Alcune osservazioni sulle relazioni tra Vegetazione e Crisidi (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae) in Italia." volume="11" year="2004">Rosa 2004</bibRefCitation>
, our own obs.). Flight period: mid-June to late August. Host: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Cerceris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cerceris rybyensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rybyensis">Cerceris rybyensis</taxonomicName>
(Linnaeus) and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Cerceris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cerceris ruficornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficornis">Cerceris ruficornis</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius) (
<taxonomicName family="Crabronidae" lsidName="" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="family">Crabronidae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Berland, L" journalOrPublisher="Paul Lechevalier, Paris" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" title="Hymenopteres vespiformes. III. (Cleptidae, Chrysidae, Trigonalidae). Faune de France, Vol. 34." year="1938">Berland and Bernard 1938</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grandi, G" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino dell'Istituto di Entomologia della Universita di Bologna" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 659" title="Studi di un entomologo sugli imenotteri superiori." volume="25" year="1961">Grandi 1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Petit, J" journalOrPublisher="Revue vervietoise d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" pagination="58 - 63" title="Les Chrysides de la faune Belge (HymenopteraChrysididae). Notes faunistiques et ethologiques. 3." volume="32" year="1975">Petit 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Univ., Tuebingen" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" title="Faunistik und Oekologie der HymenopteraAculeata des Tuebinger Gebiets, vor allem des Spitzbergs, unter besonderer Beruecksichtigung der in Holz und Pflanzenstengeln nistenden Arten. Diss." year="1979">Westrich 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brechtel, FM" journalOrPublisher="Univ., Karlsruhe" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" title="Naturschutzbezogene Erfassung der Stechimmenfauna des Bienwaldes und seiner Randbereiche (Suedpfalz) unter besonderer Beruecksichtigung der Oekologie Kunstnest-bewohnender Arten. Diss." year="1985">Brechtel 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gayubo, SF" journalOrPublisher="Graellsia" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" pagination="193 - 204" title="Efecto de la presion urbana sobre abejas y avispas en Salamanca. II. Mutillidae y Chrysididae." volume="43" year="1987">Gayubo et al. 1987</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Saure, C" journalOrPublisher="Bembix" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" pagination="15 - 18" title="Beobachtungen und Anmerkungen zur Wirtsbindung einiger Goldwespenarten im nordostdeutschen Raum (Hymenoptera: Chrysidididae: Chrysidinae)." volume="10" year="1998">Saure 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
